                      How customer reviews and ratings work

                      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

                      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

                      • Amazin Customer
                        4.0 out of 5 stars Basic watch. Not just for women
                        Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 30, 2024
                        Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
                        Although this watch describes as being for women, it fits my male wrist with plenty of room to spare. I'm guessing the gender qualification is as a result of the pink strap. Personally I don't care about that and it's easily replaced if it did bother me.

                        The watch is very basic but does what you need - telling the time and counting your steps. It keeps time even if it isn't connected to a smartphone via BlueTooth, which some don't. The ergonomics are a wee bit iffy and take some getting used to. At first I didn't think it had some of the basic functions you'd expect like timer and alarm, but I eventually found them under a submenu called "Clock". You need to have a really good play to find out all it can do as there seems to be no screen which just displays all the apps.

                        Setting it up is easy. You need to install the VeryFit app and it does the rest. The watch talks you through the process. The weak point is the app. It's one of those which has a single link to turn on all the cookies, but if you don't want them you have to spend half an hour turning off all the legitimate interests, on both the main screen and the vendors screen. I seriously hate that and find it borderline abusive and it limits my trust in the device.

                        There are a few clock faces provided by default, but there are plenty more on the app which you can select and have downloaded to the watch for free via Bluetooth.
                        Read more
